description._content:
Photograph of students from Deseronto Public School, Spring 1926.

Top row: Reg Burnham, Frank Fields, Hilliard Topping, Sherman Thompson, Gerald McWain, Keith Laughlin, Geof [?] Culhane, Francis Brennan, Gordon Green.

2nd row: Clare Dunn, Violet Whitton, Ethel Sager, Harriet McKenzie, Manley Ostrander (teacher), Eva Harvey, Blanche Smith, Ethel Abrams, Marian Martin.

3rd row: Reggie Maracle, Charlie Francis, Jake Uens, Gordon Barby, Ernie Dorey, Clifford Keech, Bruce Joyce, Lorne Abrams, Wilbert Loft.

Bottom row: Russell Farmer, John Philips, Lillian Laut [?], Vera Thompson, Jean Narmile, Isabel McAlpine, Mary Bruyea, Beatrice St Louis, Eddie St Louis.

These photographs were part of the Floyd Marlin collection. On the back of the cardboard backing to the photograph is a list of 'others' in the 1926 class:

Marguerite Ancey, Kathleen Blackburn, Elton Brant, Garfield Bruyea, Effie Clarke, Marie Genereau[x], Millie Houle, Harold Luyes, Francis Maloney, Hamel McDonald, Rebecca Lynch, Gerald Thompson, Grace Gartland, Margaret Dale, Beatrice Harvey, Herbet Hines, Muriel Moses [?]
